## Description
The** Digital Archiving Purl Ingress **resource&nbsp;allows to interact with a Digital Archiving store via API and produce a personalized URL (Purl) for an archived document.

> Note

For more information on how to define a Digital Archiving documents archive and its access endpoints, see [Digital Archiving Store Resource Reference](/doxee-platform/docs/digital-archiving-store-resource-reference).

For more information on API integration, see .

## Additional creation parameters
None.

## Resource editor
None.

## Deploy parameters
![](data:image/png;base64,)

Section

Field

Description

**Configuration**

**Tenant**

Select the&nbsp;**Tenant** on which you want to deploy the resource from the drop-down menu.

**Store**

**Resource**

Select the Digital Archiving Store resource that will be invoked when calling this endpoint.

> Important

If the selected store has not been deployed on the selected tenant, a warning message is displayed.

**Endpoint**

**Path**

Enter the final part of the URL path to call.

> Note

The custom path may include "/" characters within (e.g. **custompath** or **custompath/subpath**)

For example: "po-demo/2023-10";  the resulting URL will be: [*https://da-qa-aws-frnk-1-doxee-int.cloud.doxee.com*](https://da-qa-aws-frnk-1-doxee-int.cloud.doxee.com)*/****po-demo/2023-10****/process*

**Keys**

Select the [Ingress Credentials](/doxee-platform/docs/ingress-credentials-resource-reference) resource(s) to use for API authentication.

> Note

Up to 10 API keys can be used at the same time to avoid expiration issues.

**Parallel requests**

Enter the maximum number of allowed requests per second (default: 5).

**Extraction**

**Duration (seconds)**

*(optional)* Enter a retention period (in seconds).

**Custom domain**

*(optional)* Enter a custom domain to use for the Purl.

> Tip

Click **Publish **to publish the release on the tenant.

Click **Deploy** to publish and enable the release on the tenant.
